{
  "stem": "7739.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One day, I went on a-- on-- on-- on a-- on an expedition like this, and I found a wire full of wedding bands.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It must have been about this big, full of wedding bands.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They looked like gold to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I figured, well, I'll give it to him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, I went back, and he was quite happy what I brought him back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He sold this ring-- this-- this-- this-- this container of wedding bands for two bottles of vodka to borrow these German surveyors.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a bottle of vodka between him and the [GERMAN], the secretary of the-- of the work gang-- they must have drank it in a couple of days.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the other bottle of vodka, he took me, and he taped it to my thigh.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And of course, when we went to work there, we had to go outside of our camp on the German guard-- on the SS guard, of course, to the-- crossing the road, crossing the railway line, going into the [GERMAN] concentration camp, and there we were building the road.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And from there, we used to send us out to the ramp to organize or to steal these-- these things.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And as luck had it, on the way back to camp-- you know, when-- when you-- when you went out of the camp, orchestra plays [INAUDIBLE] martial music, and you had to march like a soldier in and march back.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so they searched us occasionally.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they found this bottle of vodka on me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was taken to the guard house, and they played with me, the SS guard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He says, oh, you [GERMAN], you know, little boy-- he says, where did you get this bottle of vodka?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, I found it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
